## Authoritative references

- PHIPA full text: <https://www.ontario.ca/laws/statute/04p03>
  (accessed 2026-05-12).
- IPC breach protocol for HICs:
  <https://www.ipc.on.ca/en/health-organizations/responding-to-a-privacy-breach/privacy-breach-protocol>
  (accessed 2026-05-12).
- Report a health-privacy breach to the IPC:
  <https://www.ipc.on.ca/en/health-organizations/report-a-privacy-breach>
  (accessed 2026-05-12).

## Definitions

- **Personal health information (PHI)** — defined in PHIPA s. 4(1).
- **Health Information Custodian (HIC)** — defined in PHIPA s. 3.
- **Agent of a HIC** — defined in PHIPA s. 2 and s. 17.
- **Breach** — for purposes of this runbook, any theft, loss, or
  unauthorized use or disclosure of PHI, *and* any unauthorized access
  to records of PHI in electronic form.

PHIPA's reporting trigger is stricter than PIPEDA's: it does not depend
on a "real risk of significant harm" test. Unauthorized access to PHI
is itself the trigger.

